# Container Creation & Settings — Crash Audit & Fixes

## Summary
Complete audit of all container creation/settings UI elements including every dropdown, checkbox, toggle, text field, and settings dialog. **7 crash-causing bugs and 3 stability issues** were identified and fixed.

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL Crashes Fixed

### 1. Graphics Driver Settings Button — Force Close (CONFIRMED)
**File**: [GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java)

**Root Cause**: `GPUInformation.enumerateExtensions()` (JNI native call) returns `null` when extensions can't be enumerated. This null array is passed directly to `MultiSelectionComboBox.setItems(null, "Extensions")` which tries `items.length` → **NPE → crash**.

**Fix**: 
- Wrapped [enumerateExtensions()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#27-28) in try-catch, returns `new String[0]` on null/error
- Added length check before calling [setItems()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/widget/MultiSelectionComboBox.java#46-54)/[setSelectedItems()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/widget/MultiSelectionComboBox.java#56-64)
- Wrapped entire [initializeDialog()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java#170-368) in try-catch blanket

### 2. [toGraphicsDriverConfig()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java#112-123) — StringIndexOutOfBoundsException
**File**: [GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java#L102-L112)

**Root Cause**: When config map is empty, the method builds an empty string then calls `substring(0, -1)` → **crash**.

**Fix**: Rewrote using `StringBuilder` with proper empty-check. Uses semicolons between entries (not trailing).

### 3. `Container.getExtra(String key)` — Wrong Data Bug
**File**: [Container.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#L311-L313)

**Root Cause**: [getExtra(String key)](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#315-323) called [getExtra(name, "")](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#315-323) using the container's `name` field instead of the `key` parameter! This returned wrong `extraData` for every single-arg lookup, potentially causing cascading failures.

**Fix**: Changed to [getExtra(key, "")](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#315-323).

### 4. DXVKConfigDialog — Static List Mutation Crash
**File**: [DXVKConfigDialog.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/DXVKConfigDialog.java)

**Root Cause**: `dxvkVersions` is a `static` field. When VKD3D version is selected, `dxvkVersions.removeAll(versions)` mutates the list **in-place** while the spinner adapter is still backed by it. On re-open or concurrent access → **inconsistent state / crash**.

**Fix**: Create filtered copy list instead of mutating the original. Applied in both [setDXVKSpinner()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/DXVKConfigDialog.java#205-230) and the `onItemSelectedListener`.

### 5. DXVKConfigDialog — ClassCastException on Save
**File**: [DXVKConfigDialog.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/DXVKConfigDialog.java#L171)

**Root Cause**: [(VKD3DVersionItem) sVKD3DVersion.getSelectedItem()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#396-404) could crash with ClassCastException if the adapter backing changes.

**Fix**: Changed to `instanceof` check before cast.

---

## 🟡 Stability Issues Fixed

### 6. Null Spinner Selections in Container Save
**File**: [ContainerDetailFragment.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java)

**Issue**: When saving, spinners with null selected items produced empty strings for `graphicsDriver`, `dxwrapper`, `audioDriver`, and `emulator` — leading to empty config values that break container launch.

**Fix**: All now fall back to `Container.DEFAULT_*` constants.

### 7. [parseIdentifier(null)](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/StringUtils.java#31-35) in [loadGraphicsDriverSpinner](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#829-872)
**File**: [ContainerDetailFragment.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#L833)

**Issue**: `StringUtils.parseIdentifier(sGraphicsDriver.getSelectedItem())` called without null check.

**Fix**: Added null check with fallback to `Container.DEFAULT_GRAPHICS_DRIVER`.

### 8. `StringUtils.parseNumber(null)` — NPE
**File**: [StringUtils.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/StringUtils.java#L36)

**Issue**: [parseNumber()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/StringUtils.java#36-39) called `.toString()` without null check.

**Fix**: Added `if (text == null) return "0"`.

### 9. Dialog Open Crash Protection
**Files**: ContainerDetailFragment.java

**Issue**: Opening [GraphicsDriverConfigDialog](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java#35-455), [DXVKConfigDialog](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/DXVKConfigDialog.java#30-302), or [WineD3DConfigDialog](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/WineD3DConfigDialog.java#22-144) could crash the app if their constructor throws.

**Fix**: All dialog `.show()` calls wrapped in try-catch with error logging.

### 10. Silent Container Save Failures  
**File**: [ContainerDetailFragment.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#L682)

**Issue**: `JSONException` was silently swallowed with `e.printStackTrace()`, giving no user feedback.

**Fix**: Added proper logging and user-facing [Toast](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/AppUtils.java#132-135) error messages.

